    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen switching sessions using plugins, sometimes it triggers errors like this:\r\n```\r\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua:55: Invalid buffer id: 22\r\nstack traceback:\r\n        [C]: in function 'nvim_create_autocmd'\r\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua:55: in function '__index'\r\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic.lua:1492: in function 'reset'\r\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp.lua:1173: in function </usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp.lua:1163>\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd also '[LSP] No client with id 1' from [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/1e7e9ee91f73c62b8c5ba9dbdabba3a3b6dc0130/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua#L582) \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n-\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeed to add some checks like `api.nvim_buf_is_valid(bufnr)` or so. \r\nTo not spam error messages.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\n-\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\npacman",
